 and Traveller accommodation to the attention of the world's media. However, as the furore surrounding the eviction has died down, the very pressing issues of accommodation need, inequality of access to education, healthcare and employment, and exclusion from British (and European) society is still very much evident. This topical book examines and debates a range of themes facing Gypsies and Travellers in British society, including health, social policy, employment and education. It also looks at the dilemmas faced in representing disadvantaged minority groups in media and political discourse, theories on power, control and justice and the impact of European initiatives on inclusion. Gypsies and Travellers: Empowerment and inclusion in British society will be of interest to students, academics, policy makers, practitioners, those working in the media, police, education and health services, and of course to Gypsies and Travellers themselves.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 0aRomaniesxCultural assimilationzGreat Britain. 0aRomaniesxSocial conditionsy21st centuryzGreat Britain. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Services & Welfare.2bisacsh1 aActon, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAllen, Dan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAvebury, Lord, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCemlyn, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFoster, Brian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreenfields, Margaret, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO’Neill, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRichardson, Joanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1